class.name: JarBASE64Encoder
class.javadoc: This is a BASE64Encoder that does not insert a default newline at the end of every output line. This is necessary because java.util.jar does its own line management (see Manifest.make72Safe()). Inserting additional new lines can cause line-wrapping problems (see CR 6219522).
Encode the suffix that ends every output line.
